com.microsoft.identity.client

Class MsalUiRequiredException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • com.microsoft.identity.client.MsalException
          • com.microsoft.identity.client.MsalUiRequiredException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public final class MsalUiRequiredException
extends MsalException
    This exception class is to inform developers that UI is required for authentication to succeed. If MsalUiRequiredException is caused by service error, claims could be possibly returned.

    Set of error codes that could be returned from this exception:

    • invalid_grant: The refresh token used to redeem access token is invalid, expired, revoked.
    • no_tokens_found: Access token doesn't exist and there is no refresh token can be found to redeem access token.
